  "prompt": "I have a Pulsar 200 NS. What would be a good re-placement for 130/70*17 rear tires?",
  "response": "Choosing a replacement for the 130/70-17 rear tire on your Pulsar 200 NS involves considering factors such as tire type, performance characteristics, and your riding style. Here are some good replacement options:\n\n1. **Michelin Pilot Street Radial** - Known for its durability and superior grip, particularly in wet conditions. It offers good stability and longevity.\n\n2. **Pirelli Diablo Rosso II** - Offers excellent grip and handling performance. It is popular among sport riders and provides good traction both in dry and wet conditions.\n\n3. **Metzeler M5 Sportec** - This tire is known for its versatile performance, providing good grip and stability. It\u2019s a well-balanced option for different riding conditions.\n\n4. **Continental ContiMotion** - A budget-friendly option that offers decent performance for everyday use, including grip and comfort.\n\n5. **Ceat Zoom Rad** - Manufactured with a focus on durability and performance, this tire is designed to handle city and highway riding effectively.\n\nMake sure to check for compatibility with local regulations and the availability of these tires in your area. Additionally, consult with a professional mechanic or tire specialist to ensure the tire you choose fits your specific riding needs and conditions.",
